{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:22.003276+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_d607162e-163d-49f9-a43c-682fc24be75e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_b9ab069e-ed61-41ca-ad13-9f286563cd3e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "7ca6ed61-cd4b-40ef-9b62-5eabc98f8a7f", "tool_call_id": "call_4bd3b8fd31ef4378827364a3", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:29.111661+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what I found:\n\n## Command-line tool installed\n\nThe package installs a CLI tool called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion), registered via the `[project.scripts]` entry in `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\n## What `gwc` currently does\n\n`gwc` is a small local-only git helper with three subcommands:\n\n| Subcommand | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| **`gwc status-summary`** | Prints a one-line summary of the current branch — its name, ahead/behind count vs. the tracked upstream, and the number of staged / unstaged / untracked files. |\n| **`gwc branch-name <issue-number> <slug>`** | Generates and prints a conventional branch name (e.g. `issue-42-add-login`). It does **not** create the branch — just prints the name for you to copy or pipe. |\n| **`gwc clean-merged [--apply]`** | Lists local branches that are fully merged into `main` (excluding protected branches). By default it's a dry-run; pass `--apply` to actually delete them. |\n\nIt also reads an optional `.gwcrc` TOML config file for customizing the branch-name prefix and the list of protected branches.\n\nThe tool intentionally refuses network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`, etc.) and history-rewriting — those are left to plain `git`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 332, "prompt_tokens": 4602, "total_tokens": 4934, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 14, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3968, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005789148, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002900748, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00028884}}, "model_provider": "